[4] Canada, airline exposure
Date: Fri 31 Mar 2017
Source: CTV News [edited]
http://bc.ctvnews.ca/airlines-warn-of-possible-measles-exposure-on-flights-1.3349747


Passengers on a [Wed 22 Mar 2017] WestJet flight from Abbotsford to Calgary are being warned that someone onboard has been diagnosed with measles.

Health officials are warning passengers who were on a number of WestJet flights, including one from Abbotsford, that they could have been exposed to the measles.

The B.C. [British Columbia] flight, WestJet Flight WS450 on [Wed 22 Mar 2017], left Abbotsford at 5:49 a.m. and arrived in Calgary at 7:50 a.m.

WestJet confirmed one of its crew members has been diagnosed with the measles. Up to 2 other cases of measles were also confirmed in Toronto.

Passengers who were on board the flights should see their doctor if they suspect they have symptoms of the highly contagious disease. See [1] above for symptoms of measles.

See URL above for WestJet or Emirates Airline flights where passengers may have been exposed.

Anyone who was on one of the following flights is advised to check their immunization records and watch for symptoms.

