[5] Europe (Italy)
Date: Fri 31 Mar 2017
Source: West [edited]
http://www.west-info.eu/measles-outbreak-among-italys-non-vaccinated/


In Italy, already in the 1st 3 months of this year [2017], 1010 cases of measles were recorded. As high as 86 percent of these were divided among 5 of Italy's regions (Piedmont, Lombardy, Lazio, Tuscany and Abruzzo) and 90 percent of the cases involved individuals who had not been vaccinated. Children in the 0--14 age range represented 26 percent of the total, and 50 of these had less than 1 year of age when they got ill.

This situation is considered an emergency that has prompted the Health Minister and Italy's National Health Institute (ISS) to disseminate a weekly bulletin in order to better monitor the phenomenon.

Measles in Italy: Weekly bulletin Update as of 28 Mar (week of 20--26 Mar)
Source: National Integrated Measles Rubella Surveillance System 1010 cases from 1 Jan 2017 90 percent unvaccinated 33 percent reported 1 or more complications 41 percent hospitalized 113 cases among health care workers Median age 27-year-old.

[Byline: Roberta Lunghini]

